00:13:32,812 --> 00:13:35,182
And, I seen these white
people walk all over him.

259
00:13:35,215 --> 00:13:37,117
He was the best man
down there at the mill.

260
00:13:37,150 --> 00:13:40,120
Walked over me too, hell I
even had to run moonshine

261
00:13:40,153 --> 00:13:41,354
one night.

262
00:13:41,388 --> 00:13:44,391
Hell I remember I
made $50 in six hours.

263
00:13:44,424 --> 00:13:46,026
$50?

264
00:13:46,059 --> 00:13:49,562
I woke up next morning
laying my uniform out

265
00:13:49,596 --> 00:13:52,599
ironed it real good,
bought me some new gloves

266
00:13:52,632 --> 00:13:54,801
and a brand new pair of boots.

267
00:13:54,834 --> 00:13:57,871
I walked in that morning,
and I told the boss man,

268
00:13:57,905 --> 00:14:01,308
"Sir, I'm here for
duty, and I'm quitting

269
00:14:01,341 --> 00:14:03,576
"at the same Goddamn time."

270
00:14:03,610 --> 00:14:04,611
That's what told him.

271
00:14:04,644 --> 00:14:05,445
Sure did.

272
00:14:05,478 --> 00:14:06,914
[Skip] Then what?

273
00:14:06,947 --> 00:14:08,157
Shit I started running
moonshine six nights a week.

274
00:14:08,181 --> 00:14:09,592
Shit, that's a lot
of money for a Negro

275
00:14:09,616 --> 00:14:10,750
back in those days.

276
00:14:10,783 --> 00:14:12,252
You can't make
that kind of money.

277
00:14:12,285 --> 00:14:13,963
Saved up enough money to
buy this place right here,

278
00:14:13,987 --> 00:14:17,557
and I ain't looked
back a day since.

279
00:14:17,590 --> 00:14:19,159
Up until right now.

280
00:14:20,027 --> 00:14:21,995
(laughing)

281
00:14:22,029 --> 00:14:24,331
Oh shit, I gotta go
introduce my next act.

282
00:14:24,364 --> 00:14:26,934
Hey Jarvis, don't you be no
stranger around here, okay?

283
00:14:26,967 --> 00:14:28,335
[Jarvis] Okay.

284
00:14:28,368 --> 00:14:31,071
Damn it if you don't
look like your daddy, Lord,

285
00:14:31,104 --> 00:14:32,605
if not more like me.

286
00:14:32,639 --> 00:14:33,974
(laughing)

287
00:14:34,007 --> 00:14:35,175
Say hey to your mom.

288
00:14:35,208 --> 00:14:36,443
Don't let us stop you.

289
00:14:36,476 --> 00:14:37,644
We just jiving Jarvis.

290
00:14:37,677 --> 00:14:39,779
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
we getting ready

291
00:14:39,812 --> 00:14:41,157
to raise some hell
up in here y'all.

292
00:14:41,181 --> 00:14:42,358
Y'all ready to have a good time?

293
00:14:42,382 --> 00:14:43,250
(cheering)

294
00:14:43,283 --> 00:14:44,184
I can't hear y'all.

295
00:14:44,217 --> 00:14:45,294
Y'all ready to have a good time?

296
00:14:45,318 --> 00:14:46,519
(cheering)

297
00:14:46,553 --> 00:14:48,421
If you feel like it,
take your clothes off.

298
00:14:48,455 --> 00:14:50,590
Just have a good time
up in here, you hear me?

299
00:14:50,623 --> 00:14:52,035
Y'all going to hell anyway
where ain't nobody going

300
00:14:52,059 --> 00:14:53,526
to church tomorrow.

301
00:14:53,560 --> 00:14:55,371
We going to have some good
time up in here, all right?

302
00:14:55,395 --> 00:14:57,030
First of all, all you men.

303
00:14:57,064 --> 00:14:58,298
[Man] Yeah?

304
00:14:58,331 --> 00:14:59,808
Keep your tongue in
your mouth, and keep

305
00:14:59,832 --> 00:15:03,370
your billfold on the table
'cause at the end of the night,

306
00:15:03,403 --> 00:15:04,537
I'm gonna get it all.

307
00:15:04,571 --> 00:15:06,473
(laughing)

308
00:15:06,506 --> 00:15:07,874
Now listen, listen up.

309
00:15:07,907 --> 00:15:10,177
I've got some special
stuff for y'all tonight.

310
00:15:10,210 --> 00:15:12,712
All right, so get ready
for the soulful sounds

311
00:15:12,745 --> 00:15:13,745
of Amaru.

312
00:15:14,814 --> 00:15:17,684
Come on, make some
noise up in here.

313
00:15:18,918 --> 00:15:23,723
♪ Come on, come on, come
on and get it, daddy ♪

314
00:15:24,591 --> 00:15:29,596
♪ While it's nice and hot

315
00:15:30,830 --> 00:15:33,400
♪ Get it while the
getting is good ♪

316
00:15:33,433 --> 00:15:35,668
♪ Baby, you're number one

317
00:15:35,702 --> 00:15:37,404
Who the hell is that?

318
00:15:37,437 --> 00:15:40,040
(dramatic music)

319
00:15:40,073 --> 00:15:43,443
Georgia Perkins,
sweet Georgia Perkins.

320
00:15:51,384 --> 00:15:55,555
The only Negro woman employed
at Jennings Paper Mill.

321
00:15:56,956 --> 00:15:59,259
She must be keeping busy at
whatever the hell she doing

322
00:15:59,292 --> 00:16:01,161
'cause I ain't never seen her.

323
00:16:01,194 --> 00:16:03,330
Nobody know exactly
what she does.

324
00:16:03,363 --> 00:16:06,933
I see her leaving
first shift everyday.

325
00:16:06,966 --> 00:16:09,336
Sometimes before the first
shift ends if I get there

326
00:16:09,369 --> 00:16:10,937
early enough.

327
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:12,672
Man, I don't give
a damn what she do.

328
00:16:12,705 --> 00:16:14,174
She could eat paper
for all I care.

329
00:16:14,207 --> 00:16:16,209
It's what I want to
do to her that got me

330
00:16:16,243 --> 00:16:18,245
feeling all warm on the inside.

331
00:16:18,278 --> 00:16:20,013
Oh Jimbo, stop.

332
00:16:20,047 --> 00:16:21,381
She ain't that kind of woman.

333
00:16:21,414 --> 00:16:22,749
Show some respect.

334
00:16:22,782 --> 00:16:23,583
What?

335
00:16:23,616 --> 00:16:24,784
Man, she can be got.

336
00:16:24,817 --> 00:16:26,386
I'm telling you all
of 'em can be got.

337
00:16:26,419 --> 00:16:28,688
Best believe that shit.

338
00:16:28,721 --> 00:16:31,124
Especially this one right here.

339
00:16:31,158 --> 00:16:32,559
Good God Almighty, damn!

340
00:16:32,592 --> 00:16:35,362
Look here, that
is a working woman.

341
00:16:35,395 --> 00:16:37,064
You see that woman
right over that,

342
00:16:37,097 --> 00:16:39,532
that fine, fine beautiful
woman over there

343
00:16:39,566 --> 00:16:40,609
sitting at that
table right there?

344
00:16:40,633 --> 00:16:42,135
She can't be bought.

345
00:16:42,169 --> 00:16:44,771
You gotta work to get that.

346
00:16:44,804 --> 00:16:47,640
It's all right for a brother
to dream sometimes though.

347
00:16:47,674 --> 00:16:49,142
Yeah.

348
00:16:49,176 --> 00:16:52,679
Hey Jericho, I bet you $2
that you won't go over there

349
00:16:53,780 --> 00:16:56,416
and see what that's
all about, $2.

350
00:16:57,484 --> 00:16:59,819
Skip, let me borrow $2, man.

351
00:17:01,954 --> 00:17:03,966
I ain't even been home
from work to clean up good.

352
00:17:03,990 --> 00:17:05,158
Jericho so what, man?

353
00:17:05,192 --> 00:17:06,459
You gonna let that get away?

354
00:17:06,493 --> 00:17:09,396
You gonna let that one pass?

355
00:17:09,429 --> 00:17:12,599
Hell no I ain't gonna
let that one pass.

356
00:17:12,632 --> 00:17:13,566
All right, damn it!

357
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:17,170
♪ Take a chance, find romance

358
00:17:17,204 --> 00:17:21,441
♪ Don't be shy, it's do or die

359
00:17:21,474 --> 00:17:26,479
♪ Come on, daddy

360
00:17:27,380 --> 00:17:31,551
♪ Come on, get it, daddy

361
00:17:32,719 --> 00:17:34,821
♪ Get it, get it,
get it, get it ♪

362
00:17:34,854 --> 00:17:37,857
♪ Get it while the
getting is good, yeah ♪

363
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:39,492
Hey handsome.

364
00:17:39,526 --> 00:17:42,395
What took you so
long to come over?

365
00:17:43,296 --> 00:17:44,997
Yeah you, silly.

366
00:17:45,031 --> 00:17:47,700
Aren't you gonna buy me a drink?

367
00:17:48,801 --> 00:17:51,538
Hell yeah, I'm
gonna buy you a drink.

368
00:17:51,571 --> 00:17:52,805
Waiter.

369
00:17:52,839 --> 00:17:55,775
(snapping)

370
00:17:55,808 --> 00:17:58,878
I'll have a slow gin fizz.

371
00:17:58,911 --> 00:18:01,448
And, I'll have a
black velvet streak.

372
00:18:01,481 --> 00:18:03,783
Didn't take you for
a whiskey drinker.

373
00:18:03,816 --> 00:18:06,819
I guess this is one of
those whiskey kind of nights.

374
00:18:06,853 --> 00:18:08,355
(laughing)

375
00:18:08,388 --> 00:18:12,292
Oh excuse me, I'll have
a monster burger as well.

376
00:18:12,325 --> 00:18:14,961
I never took you
for a burger girl.

377
00:18:14,994 --> 00:18:17,063
Well It's been a
long day at work today,

378
00:18:17,096 --> 00:18:20,500
and I just wanted something
to stick to my bones.

379
00:18:20,533 --> 00:18:22,402
God Almighty, something
sure better stick

380
00:18:22,435 --> 00:18:23,236
to your bones.

381
00:18:23,270 --> 00:18:24,737
Excuse me?

382
00:18:24,771 --> 00:18:27,507
I said I can't wait till
they play the next song.

383
00:18:27,540 --> 00:18:29,752
Well I sure do hope that
they hurry up with that burger.

384
00:18:29,776 --> 00:18:32,979
You know they're slow
as molasses around here.

385
00:18:33,012 --> 00:18:34,012
Molasses?

386
00:18:35,715 --> 00:18:38,117
(soul music)

387
00:18:48,461 --> 00:18:51,097
(bell ringing)

388
00:18:51,931 --> 00:18:53,333
(soul music)

389
00:18:53,366 --> 00:18:56,503
Jericho, pour it
on thick and heavy.

390
00:18:56,536 --> 00:18:58,938
(soul music)

391
00:19:22,128 --> 00:19:23,606
What the hell is
wrong with Jericho?

392
00:19:23,630 --> 00:19:25,232
Is he having a damn seizure?

393
00:19:25,265 --> 00:19:26,466
What's wrong with y'all?

394
00:19:26,499 --> 00:19:27,610
Y'all ain't never
seen a man dream

395
00:19:27,634 --> 00:19:29,236
about pouring something
warm and sticky

396
00:19:29,269 --> 00:19:30,470
all over a naked body?

397
00:19:30,503 --> 00:19:31,371
What the hell's
wrong with y'all?

398
00:19:31,404 --> 00:19:33,406
Well I'll be damned.

399
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:35,107
Are you all right?

400
00:19:39,779 --> 00:19:41,180
Yeah, I'm fine.

401
00:19:42,282 --> 00:19:44,617
Say, you wanna dance?

402
00:19:44,651 --> 00:19:45,985
Thought you'd never ask.

403
00:19:46,018 --> 00:19:47,287
Come on then.

404
00:19:53,360 --> 00:19:57,264
♪ Do the rooster

405
00:19:57,297 --> 00:20:00,567
♪ Shake your tail feather now

406
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:04,337
♪ Do the rooster

407
00:20:04,371 --> 00:20:07,740
♪ No matter what
the weather now ♪

408
00:20:07,774 --> 00:20:09,476
♪ Shake it up

409
00:20:09,509 --> 00:20:11,344
♪ Shake it down

410
00:20:11,378 --> 00:20:15,114
♪ Shake it till it
level with the ground ♪

411
00:20:15,147 --> 00:20:19,018
♪ Do the rooster

412
00:20:19,051 --> 00:20:22,522
♪ Shake your tail feather now

413
00:20:22,555 --> 00:20:24,757
I thought this would be
the perfect time to tell you

414
00:20:24,791 --> 00:20:26,793
that I'm an original.

415
00:20:26,826 --> 00:20:27,894
Yeah I see.

416
00:20:29,629 --> 00:20:31,264
♪ Get on up

417
00:20:31,298 --> 00:20:36,303
♪ And boogaloo, then you
gotta cock-a-doodle-doo ♪

418
00:20:37,003 --> 00:20:40,206
♪ Yeah, yeah

419
00:20:40,239 --> 00:20:42,509
All you gotta do is
keep a serious look

420
00:20:42,542 --> 00:20:44,043
on your face even
though you making

421
00:20:44,076 --> 00:20:46,413
a damn fool out of yourself.

422
00:20:58,925 --> 00:21:02,228
♪ Do the rooster

423
00:21:02,261 --> 00:21:05,197
♪ Shake your tail feather now

424
00:21:05,231 --> 00:21:08,701
♪ Do the rooster

425
00:21:08,735 --> 00:21:12,405
♪ No matter what
the weather now ♪

426
00:21:12,439 --> 00:21:14,140
♪ Shake it up

427
00:21:14,173 --> 00:21:16,008
♪ Shake it down

428
00:21:16,042 --> 00:21:20,212
♪ Shake it, shake it till
it's level with the ground ♪

429
00:21:21,614 --> 00:21:24,451
[Audience Member]
One more time!

430
00:21:29,356 --> 00:21:30,823
Oh my.

431
00:21:30,857 --> 00:21:32,992
Yeah, that's what I thought.

432
00:21:33,025 --> 00:21:35,528
Man, that's one huge burger.

433
00:21:35,562 --> 00:21:37,530
Hey, I think she gonna
need a take home bag

434
00:21:37,564 --> 00:21:40,967
'cause there ain't no
way in hell that...

435
00:21:44,371 --> 00:21:46,606
- God Damn!
- God Damn!

436
00:21:46,639 --> 00:21:48,675
You see how fast she
ate that damn burger?

437
00:21:48,708 --> 00:21:49,708
Shit!

438
00:21:51,911 --> 00:21:53,456
You must've dropped
yours on the floor

439
00:21:53,480 --> 00:21:55,448
somewhere or something.

440
00:21:55,482 --> 00:21:56,716
Don't you worry about that.

441
00:21:56,749 --> 00:21:58,751
I'll order you another
one, all right?

442
00:21:58,785 --> 00:22:00,887
There must be a crack
in this glass too.

443
00:22:00,920 --> 00:22:03,723
Baby, I'm gonna get to the
bottom of this, all right?

444
00:22:03,756 --> 00:22:04,791
You are so silly.

445
00:22:04,824 --> 00:22:05,824
I love it.

446
00:22:10,497 --> 00:22:11,498
Oh you do?

447
00:22:13,232 --> 00:22:16,068
Well let's get back to
our little discussion.

448
00:22:16,102 --> 00:22:18,137
What's a beautiful gal
like you doing working

449
00:22:18,170 --> 00:22:20,407
at a grind house like Jennings?

450
00:22:20,440 --> 00:22:22,975
Well some see it
as a grind house,

451
00:22:23,009 --> 00:22:26,145
but I don't really
see it that way.

452
00:22:26,178 --> 00:22:27,178
Oh I see.

453
00:22:29,248 --> 00:22:31,651
I don't mind them
bringing you on one bit.

454
00:22:31,684 --> 00:22:34,253
We could use another pretty
face around that place

455
00:22:34,286 --> 00:22:36,889
whether they working or
passing out sweat rags

456
00:22:36,923 --> 00:22:38,758
and tea cakes all day.

457
00:22:40,126 --> 00:22:41,528
What about you?

458
00:22:42,962 --> 00:22:45,898
Well there ain't nothing
too special about me.

459
00:22:45,932 --> 00:22:49,469
I'm just a guy that likes
to have a real good time.

460
00:22:49,502 --> 00:22:52,472
I see a beautiful gal
like you and say to myself

461
00:22:52,505 --> 00:22:54,073
why not Jericho?

462
00:22:54,106 --> 00:22:57,910
Why not go over there and see
if you can brighten her day?

463
00:22:57,944 --> 00:23:00,346
Well you certainly did that.

464
00:23:00,379 --> 00:23:02,682
But, what's your story?

465
00:23:02,715 --> 00:23:04,451
What's your mission?

466
00:23:04,484 --> 00:23:08,855
Well I got to admit
you caught me off guard

467
00:23:08,888 --> 00:23:10,523
with that one right there, baby.

468
00:23:10,557 --> 00:23:14,293
Every man has to have a
mission or a purpose in life,

469
00:23:14,326 --> 00:23:16,763
something to be
striving for, some plans

470
00:23:16,796 --> 00:23:18,865
to make a difference.

471
00:23:18,898 --> 00:23:20,933
I can see it written
all over your face.

472
00:23:20,967 --> 00:23:23,369
You look like somebody
who could really make

473
00:23:23,402 --> 00:23:25,672
a difference in this world.

474
00:23:27,073 --> 00:23:30,843
Well I got a friend named
Jarvis, and he got a mission.

475
00:23:34,046 --> 00:23:36,215
Crazy one, but at
least it's a mission.

476
00:23:36,248 --> 00:23:37,717
And, what's that?

477
00:23:37,750 --> 00:23:40,286
He wants to be the first
Negro paper press manager

478
00:23:40,319 --> 00:23:41,320
at Jennings.

479
00:23:42,188 --> 00:23:43,956
His daddy never could get it.

480
00:23:43,990 --> 00:23:46,626
He's been saying for years
he's gonna get that job.

481
00:23:46,659 --> 00:23:48,995
Old Thomas Cook senior
would be crying tears

482
00:23:49,028 --> 00:23:51,898
from the heavens above
if he ever did get it.

483
00:23:51,931 --> 00:23:55,835
There ain't no order too
tall for God if you believe.

484
00:23:55,868 --> 00:23:58,037
You do believe, don't you?

485
00:23:59,271 --> 00:24:00,406
Well...

486
00:24:00,439 --> 00:24:01,808
Now look it's getting late.

487
00:24:01,841 --> 00:24:03,042
I really have to go.

488
00:24:03,075 --> 00:24:05,678
I have to work first
shift in the morning.

489
00:24:05,712 --> 00:24:06,746
Wait!

490
00:24:06,779 --> 00:24:07,714
Can I see you again?

491
00:24:07,747 --> 00:24:09,081
Let me take you out sometime.

492
00:24:09,115 --> 00:24:11,684
Be at my job before
first shift, and we can

493
00:24:11,718 --> 00:24:16,422
talk about just where it
is you want to take me.

494
00:24:16,455 --> 00:24:21,093
Now I want to see you, so
remember don't be late.

495
00:24:21,127 --> 00:24:22,929
Oh hell no.

496
00:24:22,962 --> 00:24:25,364
I might go to Jennings right
now and spend the night.

497
00:24:25,397 --> 00:24:26,933
(laughing)

498
00:24:26,966 --> 00:24:28,300
Hot diggity dog.

499
00:24:33,239 --> 00:24:35,474
(laughing)

500
00:24:42,749 --> 00:24:44,116
Thank you, brother.

501
00:24:44,150 --> 00:24:46,285
♪ Wake up

502
00:24:46,318 --> 00:24:48,621
♪ Wake up, everybody

503
00:24:48,655 --> 00:24:53,292
♪ It's a new day

504
00:24:53,325 --> 00:24:54,627
♪ Wake up

505
00:24:54,661 --> 00:24:56,529
What's going on out there?

506
00:24:56,563 --> 00:24:58,164
Baby, baby wake up.

507
00:24:59,766 --> 00:25:00,967
You hear that?

508
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:02,000
Yeah.

509
00:25:04,003 --> 00:25:06,873
♪ Wake up, everybody

510
00:25:06,906 --> 00:25:09,642
♪ It's a new day

511
00:25:11,177 --> 00:25:14,180
Goodbye Jim Crow,
hello opportunity.

512
00:25:18,517 --> 00:25:21,487
Brother Aberdeen,
what's going on?

513
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:23,289
This is what's going on, boy.

514
00:25:23,322 --> 00:25:24,490
Read all about it.

515
00:25:24,523 --> 00:25:27,259
It's a whole new
day for opportunity.

516
00:25:27,293 --> 00:25:29,261
Thank God, thank Jesus Christ.

517
00:25:29,295 --> 00:25:30,663
He's an awesome God.

518
00:25:30,697 --> 00:25:32,999
I'll see you at the
church this evening

519
00:25:33,032 --> 00:25:36,603
for a special service,
First Negro Baptist.

520
00:25:37,704 --> 00:25:39,471
(phone ringing)

521
00:25:39,505 --> 00:25:40,505
Hello?

522
00:25:41,874 --> 00:25:43,610
Baby, it's your boss.

523
00:25:51,383 --> 00:25:53,519
Yes sir, Jarvis Cook speaking.

524
00:25:53,552 --> 00:25:55,988
Mr. Cook, I know by now
you certainly got news

525
00:25:56,022 --> 00:25:58,090
of the changes to come.

526
00:25:58,124 --> 00:26:00,627
And, you know there ain't many
of us old Southern white folk

527
00:26:00,660 --> 00:26:02,161
that's too happy about it.

528
00:26:02,194 --> 00:26:04,163
Yes sir, I understand, yes.

529
00:26:04,196 --> 00:26:06,365
But, I Mr. Cook
am not one of them.

530
00:26:06,398 --> 00:26:08,134
I'd like to offer you
my first interview

531
00:26:08,167 --> 00:26:11,638
for paper press manager at
7:30 just prior to first shift.

532
00:26:11,671 --> 00:26:12,839
Can you make it?

533
00:26:12,872 --> 00:26:14,440
Can I make it?

534
00:26:14,473 --> 00:26:15,341
Why, yes sir!

535
00:26:15,374 --> 00:26:17,209
Hey I'm on my way.

536
00:26:17,243 --> 00:26:18,377
Wonderful.

537
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:20,146
I think you'd be
perfect for the job,

538
00:26:20,179 --> 00:26:22,224
and after all, you know that
machine better than anybody.

539
00:26:22,248 --> 00:26:23,049
Thank you, sir.

540
00:26:23,082 --> 00:26:23,883
(laughing)

541
00:26:23,916 --> 00:26:25,351
You're welcome.

542
00:26:27,353 --> 00:26:28,855
(laughing)

543
00:26:28,888 --> 00:26:31,824
I just got an interview
for paper press operations

544
00:26:31,858 --> 00:26:32,725
manager.

545
00:26:32,759 --> 00:26:34,727
(laughing)

546
00:26:34,761 --> 00:26:35,761
Baby.

547
00:26:37,029 --> 00:26:39,231
♪ Wake up

548
00:26:39,265 --> 00:26:40,499
♪ Wake up, everybody

549
00:26:40,532 --> 00:26:41,710
What the hell's
going on out here?

550
00:26:41,734 --> 00:26:43,736
This is what's going on boy.

551
00:26:43,770 --> 00:26:44,937
Watch out now.

552
00:26:46,105 --> 00:26:49,842
♪ Wake up, everybody

553
00:26:49,876 --> 00:26:52,611
♪ It's a new day

554
00:26:56,749 --> 00:26:57,784
Oh my damn.

555
00:26:59,451 --> 00:27:00,451
Oh my damn.

556
00:27:02,454 --> 00:27:05,124
(phone ringing)

557
00:27:06,726 --> 00:27:08,194
Hello?

558
00:27:08,227 --> 00:27:10,196
Hey Jericho, did you see
the paper this morning?

559
00:27:10,229 --> 00:27:12,598
Hell yeah Jarvis, I seen it.

560
00:27:12,631 --> 00:27:14,566
I can't believe it.

561
00:27:14,600 --> 00:27:17,103
I've been waiting so
long for this moment,

562
00:27:17,136 --> 00:27:18,437
and it's finally here.

563
00:27:18,470 --> 00:27:21,007
The Civil Rights Acts
is making some changes.

564
00:27:21,040 --> 00:27:22,441
(laughing)

565
00:27:22,474 --> 00:27:25,077
Yes sir, this promotion's
been a long time coming for me.

566
00:27:25,111 --> 00:27:27,814
(dramatic music)

567
00:27:34,386 --> 00:27:36,088
Yeah Jarvis, that's amazing.

568
00:27:36,122 --> 00:27:37,857
Well come on, pick me up.

569
00:27:37,890 --> 00:27:39,291
Interview starting at 7:30.

570
00:27:39,325 --> 00:27:41,794
All I gotta do is show
up and the job is mine.

571
00:27:41,828 --> 00:27:45,431
Mr. Munson already know I'm
the best man for the job.

572
00:27:45,464 --> 00:27:47,233
Man, I wished you
told me earlier.

573
00:27:47,266 --> 00:27:48,744
Man, I can't come all
the way over there

574
00:27:48,768 --> 00:27:50,236
and pick you up.

575
00:27:50,269 --> 00:27:53,072
I got to hurry up and get
to work to see my baby,

576
00:27:53,105 --> 00:27:55,641
sweet Georgia Perkins
before first shift.

577
00:27:55,674 --> 00:27:57,543
[Jarvis] Sweet
Georgia Perkins?

578
00:27:57,576 --> 00:27:59,979
Didn't you just
meet up last night?

579
00:28:00,012 --> 00:28:02,614
Man, stop jiving and
bring your ass on.

580
00:28:02,648 --> 00:28:03,816
Damn it!

581
00:28:03,850 --> 00:28:05,985
Okay now Jarvis you
have your ass outside.

582
00:28:06,018 --> 00:28:07,595
Don't make me drive
all the way over there,

583
00:28:07,619 --> 00:28:09,155
burn up my gas
waiting on that porch.

584
00:28:09,188 --> 00:28:12,491
I'm gonna be ready
just bring your ass on.

585
00:28:12,524 --> 00:28:13,524
Shit.

586
00:28:15,928 --> 00:28:18,898
Damn Jarvis got me
running across town

587
00:28:18,931 --> 00:28:22,101
burning up my gas
behind his mess.

588
00:28:22,134 --> 00:28:24,703
(guitar music)

589
00:28:53,833 --> 00:28:55,835
Man, come on here, shit.

590
00:28:57,036 --> 00:28:59,638
(guitar music)

591
00:29:01,240 --> 00:29:05,411
You act like I don't live
right across the street.

592
00:29:06,412 --> 00:29:08,781
♪ Hurry, hurry, hurry on babe

593
00:29:08,815 --> 00:29:09,816
Bye, baby.

594
00:29:21,393 --> 00:29:23,896
(happy music)

595
00:29:28,567 --> 00:29:29,501
Turn on the radio.

596
00:29:29,535 --> 00:29:31,037
It's gotta be all over the news.

597
00:29:31,070 --> 00:29:34,073
Oh man, you know this radio
be going through some things.

598
00:29:34,106 --> 00:29:35,341
Never to fear.

599
00:29:35,374 --> 00:29:38,945
Look at my new trusty
pocket radio right here.

600
00:29:43,215 --> 00:29:44,583
Yes sir!

601
00:29:44,616 --> 00:29:46,061
[Radio Announcer]
Mississippi and adjoining

602
00:29:46,085 --> 00:29:47,229
Southern states are rejoicing
today with the enactment

603
00:29:47,253 --> 00:29:49,922
of the Civil Rights Act of 1964.

604
00:29:51,457 --> 00:29:53,425
This is what it's all
about right here Jericho,

605
00:29:53,459 --> 00:29:54,994
blood, sweat, and tears.

606
00:29:55,027 --> 00:29:56,863
(laughing)

607
00:29:56,896 --> 00:29:58,797
Man, it's all worth it.

608
00:29:59,966 --> 00:30:02,601
Now I can get that promotion.

609
00:30:02,634 --> 00:30:05,171
My daddy sure would
be proud of me.

610
00:30:05,204 --> 00:30:09,375
Yeah, I know he's up
there smiling right now.

611
00:30:09,408 --> 00:30:11,911
Somewhere saying
hurry up and get y'all

612
00:30:11,944 --> 00:30:15,948
narrow asses to work on
time before I smack 'em.

613
00:30:15,982 --> 00:30:18,117
Yeah that was your daddy.

614
00:30:19,285 --> 00:30:20,963
Man, don't get me all
chocked up in this car

615
00:30:20,987 --> 00:30:22,788
on the biggest day of my life.

616
00:30:22,821 --> 00:30:25,791
And, speaking of car,
when I get that job today,

617
00:30:25,824 --> 00:30:27,960
we can finally make
plans to get us one.

618
00:30:27,994 --> 00:30:30,696
Oh man, you ain't got to
wait to get some promotion,

619
00:30:30,729 --> 00:30:32,231
and have to save all that money.

620
00:30:32,264 --> 00:30:33,632
I'll just sell you mine.

621
00:30:33,665 --> 00:30:34,943
What are you talking
about this car?

622
00:30:34,967 --> 00:30:37,103
Hell yeah, I'm
talking about this car.

623
00:30:37,136 --> 00:30:40,206
Your ungrateful ass oughta be
happy I'm even considering it.

624
00:30:40,239 --> 00:30:44,310
Thanks but look this really
ain't my style, all right?

625
00:30:44,343 --> 00:30:47,146
What the hell you mean
it ain't your style?

626
00:30:47,179 --> 00:30:49,982
I'll have you know this is
a fine automobile right here.

627
00:30:50,016 --> 00:30:53,652
Hand crafted from the
finest materials in America.

628
00:30:53,685 --> 00:30:55,922
Never gave me a moments trouble.

629
00:30:55,955 --> 00:30:56,889
(car sputtering)

630
00:30:56,923 --> 00:30:57,756
Oh shit.

631
00:30:57,789 --> 00:30:59,725
(grunting)

632
00:30:59,758 --> 00:31:02,428
(dramatic music)

633
00:31:09,535 --> 00:31:11,070
Oh shit.

634
00:31:11,103 --> 00:31:12,847
[Mr. Spurling] Well
that should've been a sign

635
00:31:12,871 --> 00:31:15,274
to just call it a
day and go back home,

636
00:31:15,307 --> 00:31:17,043
but not these jokers.

637
00:31:18,310 --> 00:31:19,845
White smoke under the hood.

638
00:31:19,878 --> 00:31:21,680
That can't be good.

639
00:31:21,713 --> 00:31:24,450
(dramatic music)

640
00:31:35,694 --> 00:31:39,131
(harmonica music)

641
00:31:39,165 --> 00:31:42,534
well like I thought,
the radiator's busted.

642
00:31:42,568 --> 00:31:44,136
What are we gonna do now?

643
00:31:44,170 --> 00:31:44,971
If we don't get there
soon, I can kiss

644
00:31:45,004 --> 00:31:46,905
that promotion goodbye.

645
00:31:48,574 --> 00:31:51,043
Well Jarvis, look like we
ain't got no other choice

646
00:31:51,077 --> 00:31:52,544
but to make it on foot.

647
00:31:52,578 --> 00:31:55,347
(dramatic music)

648
00:32:06,858 --> 00:32:09,861
♪ Spirit of a black
man's struggles ♪

649
00:32:09,895 --> 00:32:11,397
♪ How you doing

650
00:32:11,430 --> 00:32:12,698
♪ We struggling, man

651
00:32:12,731 --> 00:32:15,201
♪ I seen the same
thing going on ♪

652
00:32:15,234 --> 00:32:16,868
♪ That's how the
struggle is doing ♪

653
00:32:16,902 --> 00:32:18,204
♪ They're struggling, man

654
00:32:18,237 --> 00:32:21,240
♪ I say the struggle
has all gone wrong ♪

655
00:32:21,273 --> 00:32:23,409
♪ If you wanna be baptized

656
00:32:23,442 --> 00:32:26,012
♪ Take a trip to
the other side ♪

657
00:32:26,045 --> 00:32:27,413
♪ If you wanna take a ride

658
00:32:27,446 --> 00:32:30,016
♪ And, I'll take you
there, my brother ♪

659
00:32:30,049 --> 00:32:32,718
♪ As if you down to ride

660
00:32:32,751 --> 00:32:35,087
♪ A situation lies ahead

661
00:32:35,121 --> 00:32:38,490
♪ I'll let you know

662
00:32:38,524 --> 00:32:40,826
♪ Where light is
free from pain ♪

663
00:32:40,859 --> 00:32:43,595
♪ You all can go

664
00:32:45,531 --> 00:32:48,267
(dramatic music)

665
00:32:51,237 --> 00:32:52,237
Wait.

666
00:32:55,041 --> 00:32:58,110
Look Jarvis, we'll never
make it at this rate.

667
00:32:58,144 --> 00:32:59,645
What you saying?

668
00:33:01,313 --> 00:33:03,082
I say we take
this shortcut right

669
00:33:03,115 --> 00:33:04,616
through Mr. John Edward's land.

670
00:33:04,650 --> 00:33:06,618
That old man been in a
wheelchair for years.

671
00:33:06,652 --> 00:33:08,854
He ain't ever out
to tend to his land.

672
00:33:08,887 --> 00:33:10,956
I say we cut across real
quick and make it to work

673
00:33:10,989 --> 00:33:13,859
in time to see sweet
Georgia Perkins.

674
00:33:13,892 --> 00:33:15,794
Man, have you lost your mind?

675
00:33:15,827 --> 00:33:18,264
Look it ain't no Negro
friendlies down that road

676
00:33:18,297 --> 00:33:19,465
right there.

677
00:33:19,498 --> 00:33:21,933
Have you ever heard
of Triple Lynch Mafia?

678
00:33:21,967 --> 00:33:23,311
No, I never have off
the top of my head.

679
00:33:23,335 --> 00:33:25,137
What is that a gospel
group or something?

680
00:33:25,171 --> 00:33:26,405
You trying to be funny now.

681
00:33:26,438 --> 00:33:27,915
Look word has it
they've been responsible

682
00:33:27,939 --> 00:33:29,441
for 15 hangings
around these parts

683
00:33:29,475 --> 00:33:31,910
all the way up from Minden
Hall to Piney Woods,

684
00:33:31,943 --> 00:33:34,246
and we gotta make
it to Richland?

685
00:33:34,280 --> 00:33:35,723
Now that's a long ass
way for two people

686
00:33:35,747 --> 00:33:38,784
like me and you to be walking
out in the open like that.

687
00:33:38,817 --> 00:33:40,652
It's suicide I tell you.

688
00:33:40,686 --> 00:33:43,155
We need to stick
to the safe route.

689
00:33:43,189 --> 00:33:44,423
Come on, let's go.

690
00:33:44,456 --> 00:33:45,657
So what you saying?

691
00:33:45,691 --> 00:33:47,326
You don't need that promotion?

692
00:33:47,359 --> 00:33:48,936
No, what I'm saying is
we get caught, they gonna

693
00:33:48,960 --> 00:33:52,030
hang me and barbecue
your chunky ass.

694
00:33:53,199 --> 00:33:55,234
You know why they call
them Triple Lynch Mafia?

695
00:33:55,267 --> 00:33:56,802
No, why?

696
00:33:56,835 --> 00:33:58,646
'Cause they like hanging
three Negroes at a time

697
00:33:58,670 --> 00:33:59,838
that's why.

698
00:33:59,871 --> 00:34:02,174
And, we'll be perfect
for the taking.

699
00:34:02,208 --> 00:34:03,751
Gonna have to reinforce
that rope to haul

700
00:34:03,775 --> 00:34:06,112
your thick neck ass, but
best believe we up shit creek

701
00:34:06,145 --> 00:34:07,646
if we go that way.

702
00:34:08,480 --> 00:34:10,249
Come on now.

703
00:34:10,282 --> 00:34:13,119
Why you always got to
be so damn negative, huh?

704
00:34:13,152 --> 00:34:15,321
Look if we late, you
lose your damn job.

705
00:34:15,354 --> 00:34:18,524
There ain't gonna be no
promotion, what then huh?

706
00:34:18,557 --> 00:34:20,001
You want you wife
out here selling tail

707
00:34:20,025 --> 00:34:22,027
to the white man to keep
pork chops on the table?

708
00:34:22,060 --> 00:34:23,495
Nobody gonna fire me.

709
00:34:23,529 --> 00:34:25,864
I'm the best damn paper
press operator at that job.

710
00:34:25,897 --> 00:34:27,166
Oh you want to bet?

711
00:34:27,199 --> 00:34:28,367
Yeah.

712
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:30,369
Jarvis, there's a
dozen Negroes in line

713
00:34:30,402 --> 00:34:32,771
waiting to take your
job at that plant.

714
00:34:32,804 --> 00:34:35,641
And, damn it I'm
one of 'em, shit.

715
00:34:36,742 --> 00:34:38,043
Wait.

716
00:34:38,076 --> 00:34:40,846
(dramatic music)

717
00:34:44,150 --> 00:34:46,318
You sure this a good idea?

718
00:34:47,819 --> 00:34:50,722
Jarvis, let me ask
you this one question.

719
00:34:50,756 --> 00:34:51,723
What?

720
00:34:51,757 --> 00:34:54,826
Have I ever led you wrong?

721
00:34:54,860 --> 00:34:57,529
Yeah, all the damn time, yeah.

722
00:34:58,697 --> 00:35:00,832
Well there's a first
time for everything.

723
00:35:00,866 --> 00:35:02,534
Follow my damn lead.

724
00:35:06,605 --> 00:35:10,176
Hey, hey, Jericho,
hey look at this, man?

725
00:35:11,109 --> 00:35:13,379
[Jericho] What is it?

726
00:35:13,412 --> 00:35:15,581
Ain't that Miss Johnson's
grandson that's been

727
00:35:15,614 --> 00:35:17,616
missing since last week?

728
00:35:20,286 --> 00:35:21,753
Not that I knew of.

729
00:35:21,787 --> 00:35:22,921
I can't place the face.

730
00:35:22,954 --> 00:35:23,755
Stop playing.

731
00:35:23,789 --> 00:35:25,056
You know that's him.

732
00:35:25,090 --> 00:35:26,768
Maybe I do remember
him just a little bit.

733
00:35:26,792 --> 00:35:29,094
You know maybe he got lost
or ran away from home.

734
00:35:29,127 --> 00:35:30,229
Shit, I don't know.

735
00:35:30,262 --> 00:35:31,697
Ran away from home?

736
00:35:31,730 --> 00:35:32,598
When's the last time you
ever heard of a Negro child

737
00:35:32,631 --> 00:35:34,566
running away from home?

738
00:35:36,202 --> 00:35:38,770
Well Jarvis, what
you want me to say huh?

739
00:35:38,804 --> 00:35:40,772
Remember the promotion?

740
00:35:43,975 --> 00:35:47,246
Come on, let's get
the hell outta here.

741
00:35:49,648 --> 00:35:52,418
(dramatic music)

742
00:35:56,488 --> 00:35:59,157
(car puttering)

743
00:36:14,306 --> 00:36:17,008
(dramatic music)

744
00:36:36,094 --> 00:36:37,128
Wait a minute.

745
00:36:37,162 --> 00:36:39,164
Hey, you think they saw us?

746
00:36:39,197 --> 00:36:41,333
Hell no, absolutely not.

747
00:36:41,367 --> 00:36:43,235
No way, no how.

748
00:36:43,269 --> 00:36:45,170
Then why you
running so damn fast?

749
00:36:45,203 --> 00:36:46,948
'Cause they might've
say your charcoal ass,

750
00:36:46,972 --> 00:36:48,483
and you know they think
all us Negroes look alike.

751
00:36:48,507 --> 00:36:51,610
And, I wasn't taking
no damn chances.

752
00:36:52,878 --> 00:36:54,613
[Woman] Roosevelt!

753
00:36:54,646 --> 00:36:55,646
Look.

754
00:36:57,349 --> 00:36:58,350
Roosevelt!

755
00:37:00,719 --> 00:37:03,455
(dramatic music)

756
00:37:13,131 --> 00:37:14,199
Roosevelt.

757
00:37:14,232 --> 00:37:15,334
Kitty, Kitty!

758
00:37:16,234 --> 00:37:17,303
Oh Roosevelt?

759
00:37:17,336 --> 00:37:18,770
Now where'd that cat go?

760
00:37:18,804 --> 00:37:20,806
Must've gone off yonder.

761
00:37:21,707 --> 00:37:22,708
Hey sweetie.

762
00:37:24,543 --> 00:37:26,612
Y'all are home early.

763
00:37:26,645 --> 00:37:28,780
Supper won't be ready
for at least two hours.

764
00:37:28,814 --> 00:37:30,549
I was just headed
off to Bible study

765
00:37:30,582 --> 00:37:32,484
when Roosevelt ran off.

766
00:37:32,518 --> 00:37:34,119
I don't think
that'd be a good idea.

767
00:37:34,152 --> 00:37:35,321
Well why not?

768
00:37:35,354 --> 00:37:37,889
'Cause me and the boys
is out coon hunting.

769
00:37:37,923 --> 00:37:41,192
We saw a few niggers
roaming around.

770
00:37:41,226 --> 00:37:42,628
We rushed home as
fast as we could

771
00:37:42,661 --> 00:37:44,296
to make sure y'all
was all right.

772
00:37:44,330 --> 00:37:45,631
Now where's Agnes.

773
00:37:45,664 --> 00:37:46,832
She ain't feeling well.

774
00:37:46,865 --> 00:37:48,734
She's inside nursing Cody.

775
00:37:48,767 --> 00:37:51,069
But, niggers in these parts?

776
00:37:51,102 --> 00:37:53,739
Haven't seen nobody
all day, I reckon.

777
00:37:53,772 --> 00:37:56,074
But, they know better than
to come anywhere near here.

778
00:37:56,107 --> 00:37:57,376
Hell Marcel, mama's right.

779
00:37:57,409 --> 00:37:59,077
Ain't not niggers
gonna come around here.

780
00:37:59,110 --> 00:38:00,912
They know better than that.

